</div><a id="comment-1559"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/node/376#comment-1559" class="active">Isn&#039;t this a solved problem?</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Anonymous (not verified) on Sat, 2006-04-08 18:51.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>1. Start program as root<br />
2. Bind to a low port<br />
3. setuid<br />
4. Do everything else</p>
<p>What's the problem? Can't you at least call bind() without screwing up?</p>
<p>Keep in mind that *simplicity* promotes security, while fancy complicated schemes hinder it.</p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links"><li class="first last comment_reply"><a href="/comment/reply/376/1559" class="comment_reply">reply</a></li>
